actual.value:
As the pioneer SRHR organization for the caste discriminated society, the project has been highly relevant for Dalit as it could meet the capacity requirements of the targeted staff through different activities. Also, it could support the senior management to deal with the Covid-19 in a better way. As a result, despite the postponement of activities for few months the project has achieved all its objectives with the exception of result 2.1 where the advocacy and policy strategy is yet to be formulated. As mentioned by MDF in the proposal, this would be done through the coaching sessions after the project period considering the convenience of the related staff. For result 2.2, the monitoring system upgraded by developing the M&E frameworks and results tracker; but the Knowledge Management system development is yet to happen as due to Covid-19, a lot of activities had to be done within last quarter of the extended project period. However, it is already in the action plan of the organization. On the other hand, the Covid-19 caused Dalit to focus strongly on (financial) sustainability. The staff became more confident because of the training and there have been visible changes within organization by the trained and capacitated staff. Two submitted proposals were already won in recent times. Contribution of the staff supported changes in the Gender and Safeguarding policies as well.
The change process is not always easy; it is an acculturation process which requires time and attention. To make the changes accepted and efficient, few areas could be focused by Dalit;
- Practice and apply the new knowledge and skills to enhance the capacity. - The newly formed teams as the results of the TMT; such as Business Development team, Resource Mobilization team, need to be supported and followed-up and should maintain an effective coordination between them. - The Business Development team need regular support and follow-up to ensure the progress and to establish a well-equipped business Plan. - Restructure or review the areas of intervention to cope up with the new trends and the shifted funding modalities. - Moreover, it is highly recommended that to have a plan for staff’s coaching in regular and systematic basis to support and ensure the growth of the staff and the organization.
